parameters:
Male Student: "I didn't understand today's lesson at all... At this
rate, I'm going to end up with the lowest grades in class."
Male Student: "Ah, Morisaki is here, so it's all good!"
Yui: "Haa... What do you mean by that?!"
Male Student: "Morisaki!? N-no... It's nothing, nothing at all!"

Yui: "(Honestly!... If it weren't for Zaidarg-G, I could study fairly
well myself, you know.)"

Male Student: "I'm going to get the top score in the whole grade on
the final exams in two weeks!"
Male Student: "I absolutely won't lose to that guy!"

Female Student A: "I saw Saionji-san this morning, and she seemed

\n[6]: "She's not at school either?"
\n[6]: "If that's the case, where could she be..."
Karen: "Long time no see, Amasawa-kun!"
\n[6]: "Saionji-san?"
Karen: "What have you been doing, skipping school for two weeks?"
\n[6]: "Two weeks!?"
\n[6]: "(Was I unconscious for that long...)"

Karen: "I heard you were absent without permission. That's not like
you."
\n[6]: "There's been a little situation..."
Karen: "..."

\n[6]: "That's right! Do you know where Yui might be? I can't get in
touch with her, and she doesn't seem to be at home."
Karen: "Huh?"

Karen: "Why would I know anything about her? Besides, after you turned
down my confession, you have the nerve to ask me that?"
\n[6]: "...Yeah, you're right."
Karen: "..."
Karen: "Well, fine. I'll tell you specially."

Karen: "She hasn't been coming to school either, so I don't know where
she might be."
\n[6]: "What, Yui hasn't been coming to school either?"
Karen: "But..."

Karen: "I heard some girls in class talking about seeing her walking
with Samejima."
Karen: "They even seemed to be holding hands."
\n[6]: "With Samejima?"
Karen: "You said you liked Morisaki, didn't you?"
Karen: "Could it be that you got turned down?"
\n[6]: "Why would she be with someone like Samejima..."
Karen: "Oh, it's not that surprising."
Karen: "I've dated Samejima before, so I know his charm."

Karen: "He's the tough guy type with terrible behavior, but he can be
kind sometimes."
Karen: "That gap is what some people fall for."
Karen: "It wouldn't be strange at all if Morisaki fell for Samejima."
\n[6]: "That's absolutely impossible!"
Karen: "What's with you! Don't raise your voice all of a sudden."
\n[6]: "Sorry... but Yui would never do something like that..."
\n[6]: "We've shared our feelings with each other, and then..."
Karen: "..."
Karen: "Hmm, so that happened."

Karen: "Well then, I'll tell you where Samejima's house is as a
special favor."

Karen: "If they're together, there's a high chance Morisaki is there.
Why don't you go and check it out?"
\n[6]: "Really!? That helps a lot, Saionji-san!"
Karen: "But..."
Karen: "This is personal information, you know."
Karen: "I can't just tell you for free."
Karen: "You'll have to do a little favor for me, okay?"
\n[6]: "A favor?"
Karen: "Just once, I want you to teach me how to study."
Karen: "How about it? That's not too much to ask, right?"
\n[6]: "Sorry, I don't have time for that right now..."
Karen: "One hour is enough."

Karen: "You want to know what Morisaki and Samejima are doing right
now, don't you?"

Karen: "If you indulge me for an hour, you'll probably find Morisaki
faster in the end."
\n[6]: "Will you really tell me where Samejima's house is?"
Karen: "Of course, I don't lie."
\n[6]: "Understood..."
Karen: "Thanks! \n[6]-kun!"
Karen: "Well then, shall we go?"
